<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5352.1.1>
    dc:creator "Jäger, Peter" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Revision of the huntsman spider genus Micrommata Latreille, 1804 (Sparassidae Sparassinae)" ;
    bibo:endPage "45" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-10-02" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "5352" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406890>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406899>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406907>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406909>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406925>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406931>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406944> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406890>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–3. Distribution ranges of Micrommata species. 1 M. virescens (red circles), M. diesenhoff spec. nov. (black triangle). 2 M.ligurina (red circles), M. biggi spec. nov. (black triangles).3 M. formosa (red circles), M.aljibica (black triangles). Majority of records is from specimens examined, some are from published literature or websites like iNaturalist (western record of M. aljibica, several records of M. virescens in its central range)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406890/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406899>
    dc:description "FIGURES 19–24. Micrommata biggi spec. nov., left palp (19, 22 prolateral; 20, 23 ventral; 21, 24 retrolateral) (19–21 holotype male from Ţrkiye; 22–24 male from Turkmenistan). E—embolus, TDF—tegular denticle field, TP—tegular prong." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406899/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406907>
    dc:description "FIGURES 33–38. Micrommata biggi spec. nov., habitus of preserved specimens from Ţrkiye (33, 35–36, 38 dorsal; 34, 37 ventral) (33–35 holotype male; 36–38 female paratype). Arrows indicating slight waist of median band in front of fovea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406907/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406909>
    dc:description "FIGURES 39–40. Micrommata biggi spec. nov., female paratype from Ţrkiye. 39 Epigyne, ventral. Habitus, frontal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406909/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406925>
    dc:description "FIGURES 73–83. Micrommata formosa, habitus of preserved (73–79) and live (80–83) spiders (73, 75, 78, 80, 82–83 dorsal; 74, 76, 79 ventral; 77 lateral; 81 frontal) (73–74 male from Spain; 75–77 holotype female of M. aragonensis from Spain; 78–81 female from Spain; 82 female from Malta; 83 female with opened egg sac from Portugal). Photo credits: 78–81 Arnaud Henrard; 82 Victor Falzon; 83 Sergio Henriques." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406925/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406931>
    dc:description "FIGURES 102–103. Micrommata ligurina, male from Greece (Corfu), live spider, dorsal. Arrow indicating dark foveal patch." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406931/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406944>
    dc:description "FIGURES 133–138. Micrommata virescens, adults from Germany, habitus and behaviour. 133 Male, looking for a female. 134 Female and male in the natural habitat. 135 Male and female in mating position. 136 Ditto, male bites leg of female. 137 Female with egg sac in rolled leaf of Rubus sp. 138 Egg sac with green eggs. Arrows indicating scars on the opisthosoma of female spiders. Photo credit: 136 Herbert Schirmer." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406944/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

